    {
        "name": "Cohabitant",
        "type": "discipline",
        "level": 2,
        "power": [
            "automatic"
        ],
        "action": "active",
        "maintTime": "turn",
        "tags": [],
        "flavor": [],
        "description": [
            "A willing entity of your choice within range can use your body to perform actions and vice versa. This only allows you and the target to control the actions of the other. The mental Characteristics, Base Skill Value, and any natural and innate factors of the visiting mind are used to perform any action done by the visiting mind. The host body maintains its physical Characteristics and any ability that is not a skill, like Stamina, Mana Pool, or Phenom Points.",
            "If both bodies have the Gift, the visiting mind can cast spells they know through the host body. The host body always uses their mana pool and accumulation. Spell Projection and conjuring skills use the visiting minds Base Value and any natural or innate factors it possesses.",
            "Techniques that the visiting mind has mastered can be used by the host body only if the host body has mastered the talents required to use techniques. The host body always uses their ki reserve and chakras.",
            "Martial Arts and Master Arts that the visiting mind has mastered can be used by the host body as long any talent required has been mastered by the host body.",
            "If both bodies have access to the same phenom disciplines, then the visiting mind can use that phenom with its Potential.",
            "Initiative is rolled for each body using its original mind. Action Points are tied to the body, not the mind and the body must have the Initiative to use any Active Actions.",
            "If no mind is controlling a body, it goes limp and falls to the ground. Moving a mind from one body to another must be declared during the Intention Phase. A target cannot be prevented from returning to its body. The phenom ends when the bodies are separated by a distance greater than the listed range; you and the target return to your original bodies. If one of the bodies dies, the phenom ends and the orphaned mind can remain in the other body if it was there at the time of the phenom ending. Two minds cohabiting the same body for prolonged periods of time causes degradation in the minds. Every 24 hours that two minds cohabit, they each lose one point in one of their mental Characteristics. These points only recover once the cohabitation has ended, they then recover one point each day."
        ],
